  <summary>8/2/2011--Introduced.
Calls on the people of the United States to reflect on the service of U.S. Armed Forces members deployed at home and abroad, both now and in the future. Designates October 26, 2011, as "Day of the Deployed" and encourages observing such day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.</summary>
